Everton manager, Carlo Ancelotti has tipped Liverpool as a better team compared to Manchester City this season because the Reds are yet to lose a match in the Premier League. He also described Man City head coach, Pep Guardiola as a ‘fantastic and genius’ manager who always try to do something special on the pitch. The former Napoli and Bayern Munich manager said this ahead of Everton’s Premier League clash with Manchester City on Wednesday night at the Etihad Stadium. “Liverpool have won all of the games,” Ancelotti said as quoted by Express UK. “That is why (Man City trail). It is a fantastic run but maybe Man City aren’t at the same level as last year. That’s the difference. “They remain a fantastic team with fantastic players and a fantastic manager. “It’ll be a tough test but we need confidence to compete and focus on our football. “Pep is a fantastic manager. I have a good relationship with him. “I have met him a few times. I have a lot of respect for him. “He is a genius. He always try to do something special on the pitch.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.